caption: The sushi is delish, prices are decent & Staff is very friendly. My my only complaint is that they do not open until 4pm and do not provide enough soy sauce, ever. I purchased a 5 roll special several times and got 4 packets of soy sauce, store was closed and I was out.

They are the BEST sushi place in town! We will never be happy with another! I am so glad we live around Lincoln Square. We do veggies only and they have such a variety! Sweet potato, avo asparagus cuc, shroom, gyoza! Cant get enough of it :)
My favorite sushi place.
I love getting the bowls here. Chicken terriyaki has a great grilled flavor and nice char, the beef terriyaki is good too (thin strips of marinated and cooked beef). Sushi is solid as well.

This place is lovely. Staff is super friendly. Quaint, family owned business. My go to for sushi <3 Smoothies are super fresh. You've gotta check it out. If you like avocado, try their fried avocado. It's AMAZING~!
great place to dine in , great delivery service, i recommend everything and anything your open to try my favorite if the Love roll and RnB roll

Have ordered from here during quar twice and both times food was hot and delicious when I went to pick it up. It really exceeded my expectations considering how reasonable the prices are, the agedashi tofu in particular is an absolute treat. Everything I've ordered has been fantastic and the person who managed the pickups both times was so cheerful and pleasant. Great experiences, love this place :)
Great service, delicious food! Spicy ramen was really good! I highly recommend this place!
Tracy is the best, badass-est, sweetest businesswoman, and her team makes absolutely stunning sushi. It’s our go-to spot and never disappoints.
This place has delicious food! Their outdoor patio is open. Reasonable prices! I wish they will have all you can eat as well. Recommend :)
Food and customer service is always amazing. 100% recommend this place!

Tracy is always super nice and accommodating. The food is delicious and always prepared fresh. The cost is super affordable and I’ve never been let down by their service and quality of good. Super recommend!
The food and customer service is excellent. Tracy goes above and beyond for her customers and I have never had a bad experience ordering here. Try the spicy ramen it is amazing!!

This google review is well overdue!  This is my favorite restaurant and can eat here everyday. The food is amazing and fresh. The staff is amazing and helpful always! I love the variety of rolls and the taste always blows my mind. I recommend the mango tango. Family friendly and BYOB. I recently ordered delivery and it came friend and nicely prepared.
Didn’t expect for this place to become such a regular thing but the sushi is just that good. And the Katsu Don, and the ramen... yeah it’s great and they’re so nice!

I feel I'm long overdue to give my personal review of this super friendly Japanese restaurant that specializes in sushi rolls, Japanese appetizers and ramen. This was my third visit here within the year and it's always nice and quiet every time I come here so I get the best service from Tracy each and every time.  The salmon and tuna rolls are a great value and absolutely clean and fresh tasting.  I tried a bowl of ramen which appears to come out in a rather smaller bowl but it's definitely generous in portion and incredibly affordable compared to the other ramen shops I've visited in the city of Chicago.  Tracy is very friendly and checks on with you frequently.  You can't beat the service and affordability for the quality of food you receive. If you love a casual, non rushed, non fussy "mom and pop" dining experience you will definitely appreciate Rolls N Bowls. Tracey goes well above and beyond to give you an attentive dining experience and the food here has been reliably delicious and always fairly priced.

After a year of planning to check this spot out, we finally went and it was amazing.  The atmosphere is friendly and Tracy was great. We ordered a little  of everything and it was all delicious. You can taste that everything's made fresh,  right down to the sauces. We will definitely be making Rolls N Bowls a regular stop for lunch dates. If you haven't already gone, GO!!
My favorite chicken teriyaki bowl! Always great service, too.
The food is awesome And the sushi is the bomb!!!

The ramen and udon noodles were good, however the broth for both could've been a bit more flavorful. Trying the tempura vegetables is a must, they are to die for. The waitress was super friendly and welcoming, and the place was well kept and neat. Great experience here. I'd come back again.

The apps are kind of the star of this place!  There are some pretty diverse menu options and the overall vibe of the restaurant is really cool.  The service was good, the staff were nice and the place is clean.  The ramen was fine - pretty standard.  If this is close and you need a fix, it's a good spot.

Tracy was super helpful in helping me and my date select our desired meal. I normally don’t write reviews, but you must check this place out! (Right next to LSAC, this is insanely good post/pre-workout food if you need healthy food for your exercise program)

The food itself was excellent, everything was beautifully seasoned and cooked. The maki, especially the salmon, was incredibly fresh and bursting with flavor.  However, the appetizer we ordered came out after I had already finished my entree, and our specialty roll came out after we had already finished our dessert. There was about a 15 minute lull between the two entrees in which one of us had food and the other didnt. The menu was inconsistent, the ramen just a bowl of 99 cent brick ramen without much care put in to it while the beef appetizer was like a painting on a plate.  The incredibly poor timing really detracted from the otherwise stellar food, and made for a disappointingexperience. 3 out of 5.
This spot is awesome! Fair rates, large dishes and the staff are constantly super nice.
Get their stuffed avocado, that is sooo good! And the staff are so kind. Definitely going back! I think we found our sushi place in the neighborhood
Nice restaurant with great service
Some delicious sushi and miso soup.

Really strong flavors and beautifully presented. I had the Katsu Don and Tempura Ice. They also gave us Miso Soup. It was great in general, but even better because of its affordable price. Would definitely recommend.
Great food. Friendly service as always.
Got the gyoza, spicy ramen with shrimp❤, bf got the regular ramen and it was all delicious! Definitely recommend they have never disappointed me
Great place to quench a craving for ramen!  Had their ramen with beef and I ate two bowls!!! Absolutely delicious.
Literally the best sushi place ever in history I totally recommend this place is so awesome is so beautiful inside it's so comfortable it's small but Spacey it's just perfect all around
Loved it ❤️
Great food. Excellent service

the food here is really worth the price! only about $5 for a bowl of ramen. a chirashi bowl is only $18. it's pretty good quality too. the only downside was that we had to wait around 30 minutes for them to prepare the food, even though we went at 6 pm when they weren't very busy.
Awesome sushi and great noodle dishes!!! And it is BYOB...
Awesome food, awesome employees. We've since moved and the cravings for a teriyaki bowl can be overwhelming sometimes. We miss you, Phil!
Had the most delicious sushi here, came on a Sunday night at 8:45 and even at that time everything was fresh and delicious. HIGHLY recommend worth every penny.
Ordered from here today, everything was fresh and plentiful. Will be coming back!
Convenient. Sometimes made with different ingredients so make sure to ask. Love their bowls.
I love everything I get here! The service is slow sometimes
Nice servers...good food
Waiter was very rude today!
Cozy and unique.

We just love coming here. I've had such wonderful food at this place. This time at our table, we shared an appetizer of shrimp and vegetable tempura, I got the beef teriyaki dinner and my friends got the chicken teriyaki dinner. As always, everything was stupendous. I think they have the best teriyaki sauce just ever.

I never jump quickly to write a bad review but today’s lunch forced me to it - Spicy Beef Udon Soup .... what a mistake this watery substance was. Meat that I could  not even chew and a watered down taste of the $.99 store purchased Chinese instant hot soup. Had to send it back and they still tried to charge me for the soup I couldn’t eat because it was so bad. I asked to see the manager in order for it to be removed from my bill and the owner stated : “if it’s not salty enough for you start cooking at home” and when I refused to pay Police was called. My jaw completely dropped when she accused me of being a racist trying to take an advantage of her just because she is Asian ! 😳 Unreal mind blowing experience. No wonder this place is empty. Left a $20 bill and walked out. Never again. If you like tasteless food and rude management that calls you names this is a place for you ! Edit: Few hours after this incident me and my wife both are shaken up and feel bad that someone would use their position of being a business owner and force us to pay for a meal that was send back to the kitchen uneaten - we almost feel robbed. It is not about the money, it’s only a stupid ten bucks- it is about a really bad attitude of the owner holding you hostage and demanding the payment for the food you don’t wanna eat.

This place has placed above and beyond expectations for me! The food all was out very quick and was at the highest quality. For the price that I paid I definitely would recommend it to anyone that’s looking for higher quality at a very convenient price. My server was beyond amazing and I’ll definitely keep coming back!
Great service excellent bubble teas and noodles
Great service and good food. The place has a nice ambiance to it. The rolls and soup were really good. It's a nice quaint place.
Nemesio and Tracy provide the finest sushi in Lincoln square. Make sure to try the Miso soup and get a pot of tea. The Charashi salad is the jewel of this menu.
Very tasty sushi and friendly staff. Quick service. Only downside, no airconditioning.
The prices are not that good but when you can't find something you want that's old they might just have it for you.
Great fast service and very friendly staff. A great meal before a movie
Great place for sushi, very clean and the Food is good, friendly atmosphere.
One of the Best in town, with Unbeatable prices food Is always outstanding if you like Japanese food this is the best in the city!
Never fun when you walk 15minutes in 20degree weather to enjoy some hot ramen, only to find that even though you checked online... they’re not open!!
The sushi is good. Green bean and sweet potato are the kids favorite. They have great ramen and chicken teriyaki too. Friendly staff and always a go to in the square
Surprisingly good ramen bowls and great sushi. Waiter was excellent as well.
Great service - Beef teriyaki bowl to die for. Wonderful atmosphere.
Good food and fast.
Lovely service with delicious food

My friends and I went here for dinner before a concert.  It was delicious, cheap, and fast - I and another friend each had udon, which came out nearly too hot to eat (as they should be) and were both delicious.  Another friend ate his bulgogi bowl so quickly I honestly barely saw it.  Would definitely go back.
The bulgogi bowl was delicious and was the perfect portion size
Food was delicious, employees were nice.

The bowls might all be really simple, just rice and meat. The rolls were good. Would go back though and explore the menu more. We also enjoyed the atmosphere. BYOB was nice.

The servers are very nice and deserve good tips! The food quality and presentation were amazing and the taste of it all was GOOD!

Really good service and excellent sushi

(05/29/2015) Wasn't feeling 100% this week so my husband brought me to Rolls 'n Bowls for a quick bowl of udon soup. They're generous with the broth but generally I prefer eating the noodles only lol. This soup could use a little more flavor but it definitely filled me up 🍜

They have the best miso soup I've ever had. I had the spicy udon noodles and they had just the right amount of bite; they were perfect. The atmosphere is cozy, the staff is friendly and knowledgeable, and the food is excellent. This is a quaint little Japanese restaurant in Lincoln Square; can it get any better? 10/10! Highly recommended. Will definitely be back.
Excellent food

Quaint little Japanese sushi and noodle place in Lincoln Square. Large booths and great service but BYOB. Spring rolls were refreshing and light. Typical variety of sushi creations but the Love Sushi Rolls are unique and camera ready. First Mexican roll that actually uses enough jalapeños make it hot. Extremely fresh sashimi Tako and Sake. One of the cleanest restaurants in the entire Square, too.
Best sushi i have ever tried
Fast, tasty, affordable
This place is awesome. Great, friendly service & laid back 'fast-casual' atmosphere.

Best sushi in Lincoln Square! Come here and order the Mexican Maki roll, the Crazy  Sumo, and the Samurai roll! Make sure you squirt lime juice on the Mexican roll! This is a great place to grab "quick" sushi. No waiters..."fast food" style...place your order...and take a number. The complete opposite of over pretentious. Get the Fried Green Tea Ice Cream!
